janus-server has been installed under:

    /opt/janus-server

Next steps:

1. Edit the server config:

       vi /opt/janus-server/etc/server.toml

   At minimum, set:

       [server]
       public_base_url = "your-ci-hostname.example.com"

       [auth]
       session_secret = "replace-this-with-a-long-random-secret"

2. Initialize runner signing keys:

       /opt/janus-server/bin/janus-server admin runner-key init \
         --config /opt/janus-server/etc/server.toml

3. Bootstrap the first admin user:

       /opt/janus-server/bin/janus-server admin bootstrap-admin \
         --username admin \
         --config /opt/janus-server/etc/server.toml

4. Enable and start the service.

   Either add the package rc directory to local_startup:

       sysrc local_startup="/usr/local/etc/rc.d /opt/janus-server/etc/rc.d"
       sysrc janus_server_enable=YES
       service janus_server start

   Or symlink the rc script into /usr/local/etc/rc.d:

       ln -s /opt/janus-server/etc/rc.d/janus_server /usr/local/etc/rc.d/janus_server
       sysrc janus_server_enable=YES
       service janus_server start

5. For Git-over-SSH, add this block to sshd_config:

       Match User git
           PubkeyAuthentication yes
           PasswordAuthentication no
           X11Forwarding no
           AllowTcpForwarding no
           PermitTTY no
           ForceCommand /opt/janus-server/libexec/janus-git-ssh

   Put Git SSH public keys in:

       /opt/janus-server/home/git/.ssh/authorized_keys

   Then restart sshd:

       service sshd restart

Logs are written to:

    /opt/janus-server/log/janus_server.log
